msgid ""
"With this ``TSPluginInit`` routine, the plugin is called back every time "
"Traffic Server reads a response header."
msgstr ""

# 953e43ac572241efbcb9b716b8f11c79
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/http-transformations/sample-buffered-null-transformation-plugin.en.rst:49
msgid "Checks to see if the transaction response is transformable."
msgstr ""

# 2c29c15ff3ff4427bbe22552714390f1
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/http-transformations/sample-buffered-null-transformation-plugin.en.rst:61
msgid ""
"The default behavior for transformations is to cache the transformed "
"content (if desired, you also can tell Traffic Server to cache "
"untransformed content). Therefore, only responses received directly from "
"an origin server need to be transformed. Objects served from the cache "
"are already transformed. To determine whether the response is from the "
"origin server, the routine transformable checks the response header for "
"the \"200 OK\" server response."
msgstr ""

# 3c2b67aeae6e4112987d1f074e6278d8
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/http-transformations/sample-buffered-null-transformation-plugin.en.rst:88
msgid ""
"If the response is transformable, then the plugin creates a "
"transformation vconnection that gets called back when the response data "
"is ready to be transformed (as it is streaming from the origin server)."
msgstr ""

# 89c1f80adbc6431c83f6066aa08c9098
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/http-transformations/sample-buffered-null-transformation-plugin.en.rst:102
msgid ""
"The previous code fragment shows that the handler function for the "
"transformation vconnection is ``bnull_transform``."
msgstr ""

# b96ee927d2ca41f8b00f25cf1055a7f5
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/http-transformations/sample-buffered-null-transformation-plugin.en.rst:105
msgid ""
"The ``bnull_transform`` function has to handle ``ERROR``, "
"``WRITE_COMPLETE``, ``WRITE_READY``, and ``IMMEDIATE`` events. If the "
"transform is just beginning, the event received is probably "
"``IMMEDIATE``. The ``bnull_transform`` function calls "
"``handle_transform`` to handle ``WRITE_READY`` and ``IMMEDIATE``."
msgstr ""

# 692fd90d8d2a419a8fe6fb0d27049060
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/http-transformations/sample-buffered-null-transformation-plugin.en.rst:111
msgid ""
"The ``handle_transform`` function examines the data parameter for the "
"continuation passed to it (the continuation passed to "
"``handle_transform`` is the transformation vconnection). The data "
"structure keeps track of two states: copying the data into the buffer "
"(``STATE_BUFFER_DATA``) and writing the contents of the buffer to the "
"output vconnection (``STATE_OUTPUT_DATA``)."
msgstr ""

# 72d1dbf7cced45218a6ff8fc1b6fa721
